article.headline: Cleveland St. 65, Wright St. 46
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Norris Cole scored 14 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Jeremy Montgomery scored 17 points to lead Cleveland State over Wright State 65-46 on Saturday. The Vikings (18-3, 7-2 Horizon League) held Wright State to 26.8 percent shooting (11 of 41) in winning a school-record 14th straight game at the Wolstein Center. Cleveland State, which jumped out to a 9-2 lead and led the entire way, outrebounded the Raiders 39-20. The Vikings turned it over 17 times but overcame that at the free-throw line. Cleveland State made 92 percent from the line (23 of 25), including 16 of 16 in the second half. Aaron Pogue added 15 points for Wright State, which scored 10 straight to lead by as many as 24, 63-39, on Josh McCoy's free throws with 3:23 remaining. Vaughn Duggins scored 14 points to lead Wright State (13-8, 6-3), which had won six of seven heading in.
